      "note_no": "186",
      "note": "There are rules of course for the disposal of intestate property. But it is a good thing that a dying man or woman should, of his own free will, think of his parents and his next of kin, not in a spirit of injustice to others, but in a spirit of love and reverence for those who have cherished him. He must, however, do it \"according to reasonable usage\": the limitations will be seen further on."
