  "en_notes_asad": [
    {
      "note_no": "152",
      "note": "The word khayr occurring in this sentence denotes \"much wealth\" and not simply \"property\": and this explains the injunction that one who leaves much wealth behind should make bequests to particularly deserving members of his family in addition to - and preceding the distribution of - the legally - fixed shares mentioned in 4:11-12. This interpretation of khayr is supported by sayings of 'A'ishah and 'Ali ibn Abi Talib, both of them referring to this particular verse (cf. Zamakhshari and Baydawi)."
